The program prompts the user for a CSV file path, reads and parses the file line-by-line using a custom CSV parser that handles quoted fields, and stores valid records in a list. It then analyzes the data to compute basic statistics, including total records, unique candidate names, score ranges and averages, pass/fail counts, and duplicate row detection based on exact string matching. Finally, it displays frequency counts for each column, showing the number of distinct values and their number of occurrences. The program uses standard Java collections like HashMap and HashSet for efficient data processing and handles errors during file reading.